As of February 10, 2025, here are the latest election results:

Kosovo Parliamentary Election

Kosovo's ruling party, Vetevendosje, is projected to win the parliamentary election but did not secure an absolute majority, garnering 41.3% of votes with 88% of ballots counted. This marks a decline from the over 50% achieved in 2021. Prime Minister Albin Kurti will likely lead the next government, facing key issues such as relations with Serbia and the integration of ethnic Serbs in northern Kosovo. The opposition Democratic Party of Kosovo and Democratic League of Kosovo received 21.8% and 17.8% of votes, respectively. 
REUTERS

United States Presidential Election

Former President Donald Trump has been elected as the next president of the United States, defeating Vice President Kamala Harris in the 2024 presidential race. Trump secured critical battleground states like Georgia, North Carolina, and Pennsylvania, disrupting Harris's path to victory. Voters prioritized democracy and the economy as pivotal issues, with Trump's campaign gaining momentum closer to Election Day. 
THE IRISH SUN

United Kingdom General Election

The United Kingdom held its general election on July 4, 2024. Labour achieved a landslide victory, securing 411 seats out of 650, while the Conservatives won only 121 seats, marking their worst result since the early 19th century. The Liberal Democrats made significant gains, reaching their highest ever number of seats. This election was notable for its low voter turnout and the first under the reign of King Charles III. 
WIKIPEDIA, THE FREE ENCYCLOPEDIA

Namibian General Election

Namibia held its general election on December 1, 2024. Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah was declared the winner with 57% of the vote, becoming the first woman to be elected as president of Namibia. The ruling party, SWAPO, received its weakest showing since Namibia's independence, barely securing a majority in parliament. 
WIKIPEDIA, THE FREE ENCYCLOPEDIA

Ireland General Election

Ireland held its general election in December 2024. Fianna FÃ¡il and Fine Gael are set to secure over 80 seats combined, just short of the 88 needed for a parliamentary majority. Sinn FÃ©in, initially leading in exit polls, is expected to win around 40 seats, making it unlikely to form a coalition. Fianna FÃ¡il and Fine Gael have ruled out partnering with Sinn FÃ©in, indicating another coalition between themselves. 
THE TIMES & THE SUNDAY TIMES

Georgia Parliamentary Election

Georgia held its parliamentary elections on October 26, 2024. The ruling Georgian Dream party purportedly won 53.93% of the vote. Opposition supporters have rejected the results, alleging vote-rigging, and have staged protests outside the commission's building in Tbilisi. European observers noted bribery, double voting, and violence during the elections. 
AP NEWS

Please note that election results can evolve as official counts are finalized and legal challenges are resolved. For the most current information, refer to official election authorities or reputable news outlets.
